						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1462, Vikāri, Pushya, ba. 5,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1539 December 29, Monday</hi> (not verifiable), in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Achyutarāya-Mahārāya.</hi> It records that the <hi rend="italic">Pradhāna</hi> <hi rend="bold">Mallapayya</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Kāḷapa</hi> made a gift of land to Brāhmaṇas and Jaṅgamadēvas in the presence of the god Nañjuṇḍēśvara.</p>						

